            . I am a shoe-maker, and live in Hatton-garden, the prisoner was in my service; and on the first of December, about half-past nine o'clock, I saw him go out, and suspecting he had something, I stopped him, and took him to Barnley, who found three pair of shoes on him, in my presence - they are mine, and were in the shop the night before.</p>
